\n\n# Creative volume is a structural advantage\n\nAcross industries and budget sizes, one pattern is consistent. **Advertisers that launch more ads get more winners. **\n\nThis doesn’t mean they are better at predicting what will work. It means they are running more tests in an environment where wins are rare.\n\nAd performance on Meta behaves like probability. Roughly half of all ads don’t receive spend — or they receive very minimal amounts of spend. Meanwhile, 6% of ads are responsible for the majority of the spend in any given account. Put simply, a very small number of ads “work.” Each new ad that an advertiser launches is another chance to find one of these standouts.","class":"part-1-search-for-winners","name":"Part 1: The Search for Winners","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":223,"name":"volume-and-outliers","class":"volume-and-outliers","chart":{"id":29,"documentId":"wg4laldui8pqbpmdnek1wprq","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-volume-and-outliers","createdAt":"2026-02-13T23:11:39.276Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-04T19:41:58.349Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-04T19:41:58.742Z","title":"Winners become more common as volume rises, indicating testing increases the odds of breakout ads.","subtitle":"Relationship between weekly ad volume and number of winning creatives across advertisers. Toggle by monthly ad spend."},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4012,"body":"What separates stronger advertisers is not sharper intuition. It’s how their testing cadence works. They create enough new ideas to give wins a chance to appear, and they notice when something starts to take off.\n\nThis pattern shows up even when comparing advertisers with similar budgets. Bigger budgets allow more testing, but the pace of launching new ads explains the difference between top-performing brands and everyone else. \n\nIn simple terms, volume helps because it creates more opportunities to get winners. It doesn’t make the average ad better. It increases how often an advertiser runs into something exceptional. \n\n In a system where big wins are uncommon but crucial, taking more chances matters more than being certain about any individual ad.
\n\n# \n\n# Winners are rare — and that’s okay\n\nIf spend was more evenly spread out, improving results would mostly be about optimization. The data shows that’s not how it works. Most ads don’t spend, or they spend very little. Meanwhile, a small number of ads receive far more spend than the rest.","class":null,"name":"What separates stronger advertisers","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":224,"name":"many-ads-spend","class":null,"chart":{"id":4,"documentId":"v9mnta3q9lwzxtr1oacq0ygw","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-many-ads-spend","createdAt":"2026-02-13T23:12:33.209Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-13T23:12:33.209Z","publishedAt":"2026-02-13T23:12:33.372Z","title":null,"subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4013,"body":"This isn’t just a holiday effect. It’s not a sign of bad creative decisions. It’s how performance advertising behaves. \n\nIn this report, we use a strict definition of a winner . In order to become a winner, an ad must spend at least 10× more than the account’s median ad. This helps us find ads that truly stand out, not just ads that run a bit longer.\n\nAs accounts get larger, the bar gets higher. Bigger brands run more ads and spend more overall. That raises the level of spend an ad must reach to stand out compared to the account average. Winners grow unevenly as volume increases.","class":null,"name":"This isn’t just a holiday effect.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":225,"name":"testing-volume-hit-rate","class":null,"chart":{"id":31,"documentId":"da54d788n5xway3ophajh813","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-testing-volume-hit-rate","createdAt":"2026-03-03T04:54:03.517Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-05T19:26:39.555Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-05T19:26:39.972Z","title":"Testing Volume and Hit Rate","subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4014,"body":"This helps explain a common frustration. When results are predictably inconsistent, it doesn’t always mean an ad that doesn’t spend is “weak.”\n\nIt suggests that advertisers are much better off asking themselves why an ad worked than why it didn’t. Because the majority of ads will predictably fail, understanding your winners has significantly greater impact on your account than interrogating “losing” ads.","class":null,"name":"This helps explain a common frustration.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":4015,"body":"# Rethinking hit rate\n\n Hit rate is often used as a scorecard for creative strategists. A high hit rate can look like proof that a marketer knows what will work. It can be treated as a measure of someone’s intuition or quality of judgement. \n\nBut on the contrary, high hit rates may actually signal that someone isn’t testing enough to maximize their accounts’ potential. \n\nTwo accounts can have the same hit rate but work very differently. One might launch only a few ads and put most of their spend behind them. Another might test many ads and find a few strong outliers along the way. Hit rates are likely to look lower for the latter, despite more testing.","class":"rethinking-hit-rate bump-top","name":"Rethinking hit rate","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":3122,"class":"why-hit-rate-can-be-misleading","caption":null,"title":null,"name":"Why hit rate can be misleading","href":null,"href_target":null,"body":null,"layout":null,"smallscreen":{"id":267,"documentId":"vy5euqjnku992vajmkwl276e","name":"why-hitrate-can-be-misleading-smallscreen.svg","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":390,"height":305,"formats":null,"hash":"why_hitrate_can_be_misleading_smallscreen_e132257813","ext":".svg","mime":"image/svg+xml","size":86.79,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/why_hitrate_can_be_misleading_smallscreen_e132257813.svg","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.144Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.144Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.144Z","focalPoint":null},"image":{"id":234,"documentId":"agty7w8iy6kgkw6nhlu8dim2","name":"why-hit-rate-can-be-misleading.svg","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":582,"height":436,"formats":null,"hash":"why_hit_rate_can_be_misleading_e4c40e9b57","ext":".svg","mime":"image/svg+xml","size":86.69,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/why_hit_rate_can_be_misleading_e4c40e9b57.svg","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:00:27.270Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T05:00:27.270Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T05:00:27.270Z","focalPoint":null},"__component":"shared.image"},{"id":4016,"body":"This is why high hit rates need context. They could mean strong judgment. They can also mean limited testing. The metric itself cannot tell you which is true. Lower hit rates often appear in accounts that test more ideas. More testing naturally produces more average ads as well as more winners.\n\nHit rate is still a valuable metric. But it is not a proxy for success. It just describes how often rare events happen within an account.","class":null,"name":"This is why high hit rates need context.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":4017,"body":"# Mid-range spenders and portfolio logic\n\nBetween winning ads and losing ads sits a third group that often gets less attention: mid-range spenders. \n\nThese ads are not outliers. They never become winners. But they keep running, receive steady spend, and in many accounts they quietly support day-to-day performance.\n\nThe chart below shows how ads are split between three groups: losing ads, mid-range ads, and winners. Across spend tiers, mid-range ads make up a considerable share of active ads.","class":"bump-top","name":"Mid-range spenders and portfolio logic","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":226,"name":"winning-ads-make-up","class":null,"chart":{"id":8,"documentId":"yk4gkxd3y1bahkxslxzm6wxx","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-winning-ads-make-up","createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:03:04.191Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T05:03:20.871Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T05:03:21.134Z","title":"Winning ads make up a small share of portfolios, even for higher-spend advertisers.","subtitle":"Percentage breakdown of losing ads, mid-range spenders and winners by monthly ad spend."},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4018,"body":"The chart below looks at how spend is distributed across these portfolios. Here, a clear pattern appears. While winners typically absorb the largest share of spend, mid-range ads still carry a meaningful proportion of spend — particularly in smaller accounts.","class":"the-chart-below padding-top-zero","name":"The chart below looks at how spend is distributed across these portfolios.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":227,"name":"ad-spend-shifts","class":null,"chart":{"id":10,"documentId":"avuq1cb5q0givg6ulxvmgqcy","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-ad-spend-shifts","createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:05:28.310Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T05:05:39.227Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T05:05:39.558Z","title":"Ad spend shifts toward winners as accounts grow, rather than spreading evenly across creatives.","subtitle":"Percentage of spend going to losing ads, mid-range spenders, and winners by spend tier."},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4019,"body":"These mid-range spenders play a different role than winners. They don’t spike performance. But they help keep spend stable.\n\nLarger accounts often behave like volatile portfolios. Some ads aim for big gains. Others provide consistency. Winners can drive growth, but they are unpredictable. \n\nSmaller accounts, on the other hand, depend more on stability. They have less budget for big swings and rely more heavily on sure bets. \n\nMid-range spenders make high testing volume easier to manage. When teams launch many ads, some will fail quickly. Without stable ads in the mix, that churn can create volatility. Mid-range ads act as a ballast. \n\nA common mistake is to treat mid-range ads as failed tests. In a healthy account, they connect testing and scaling. They help keep performance steady while new ideas compete for spend.","class":null,"name":"These mid-range spenders play a different role than winners.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":3123,"class":"bubble-caption","caption":null,"title":null,"name":"A common mistake is ...","href":null,"href_target":null,"body":null,"layout":null,"smallscreen":{"id":268,"documentId":"vvgt0faclon74npwdu24f6yi","name":"cb2026-a-common-mistake-smallscreen.svg","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":390,"height":456,"formats":null,"hash":"cb2026_a_common_mistake_smallscreen_400bfa62fd","ext":".svg","mime":"image/svg+xml","size":260.53,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/cb2026_a_common_mistake_smallscreen_400bfa62fd.svg","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.254Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.254Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:19.254Z","focalPoint":null},"image":{"id":235,"documentId":"ivko68day4y2p71xefg7vra4","name":"cb2026-a-common-mistake.svg","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":927,"height":248,"formats":null,"hash":"cb2026_a_common_mistake_2e28482432","ext":".svg","mime":"image/svg+xml","size":261.23,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/cb2026_a_common_mistake_2e28482432.svg","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:07:20.770Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T05:07:20.770Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T05:07:20.770Z","focalPoint":null},"__component":"shared.image"},{"id":4020,"body":"# How many ads should you be testing?\n\nThere’s no universal testing volume that’s “best” for all advertisers. The right testing volume depends on budget, team size, and how quickly an advertiser can produce new ideas.\n\nCreative output varies widely across accounts. Some advertisers launch only a few ads per week. Others launch many more. This reflects resources and workflow as much as strategy.\n\nBelow are the median testing volumes listed out by vertical and by spend tier.","class":null,"name":"How many ads should you be testing?","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":228,"name":"average-weekly-testing-volume","class":null,"chart":{"id":32,"documentId":"sfdbxj9gu63v5pcwotec2btn","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-average-weekly-testing-volume","createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:09:57.132Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-05T19:28:10.877Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-05T19:28:11.503Z","title":"Average weekly testing volume by industry vertical","subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4021,"body":" Creative volume rises with scale. As advertisers move up spend tiers , they typically launch more ads per week, surface more winners, and show higher average hit rates.\n\nThis reflects organizational capacity as much as budget. Larger advertisers are not simply spending more, they are building systems that support faster testing.\n\nWithin each spend tier, the pattern still holds. Top advertisers ship materially more creative than average. And the gap is not marginal.","class":"creative-volume-rises","name":"Creative volume rises with scale.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":229,"name":"Top Advertiser Volume","class":null,"chart":{"id":33,"documentId":"l40j1wnuwjud61ppgpns69y6","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-top-advertiser-volume","createdAt":"2026-03-03T05:22:04.341Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-05T19:28:54.256Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-05T19:28:54.635Z","title":"Top Advertiser Volume","subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4022,"body":"For a smaller advertiser, testing a handful of ads per week may be enough to get winners. For a mid-market or growth-stage brand, that level of output is unlikely to produce enough surface area to generate as many winners as they could. \n\n**At larger scales, conservative testing virtually guarantees that winners will be rare because shipping volume is not designed to find them.**\n\nThe most useful question creative strategists should be asking is **are we shipping enough ads to make winners possible?**\n\nMany teams anchor output to comfort — what production and approval workflows can easily support. Our research suggests that this constraint is often organizational. \n\nCreative strategy should be seen more as capacity planning than optimization.","class":"a-smaller-advertiser","name":"For a smaller advertiser ...","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":92,"header":"Want to uncover the \"why\" behind your winners?","body":"Motion's AI will identify your winners, then tell you what makes them tick. ","class":"secondies","name":"Want to uncover the \"why\" behind your winners?","button":[{"id":356,"text":"Book a demo","url":"https://motionapp.com/book-a-demo","buttonstyle":null,"unfurler":false,"target":null},{"id":357,"text":"Start free trial","url":"https://projects.motionapp.com/signup","buttonstyle":"hollow","unfurler":false,"target":null}],"graphical_accompaniment":{"id":3124,"class":null,"caption":null,"title":null,"name":null,"href":null,"href_target":null,"body":null,"layout":null,"image":{"id":232,"documentId":"q3j44qd98whtfmwiiv4eks1v","name":"cb2026-demo-trial-2026-03-02.png","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":846,"height":642,"formats":{"small":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/small_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea.png","hash":"small_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea","mime":"image/png","name":"small_cb2026-demo-trial-2026-03-02.png","path":null,"size":320.7,"width":500,"height":379,"sizeInBytes":320696},"medium":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/medium_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea.png","hash":"medium_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea","mime":"image/png","name":"medium_cb2026-demo-trial-2026-03-02.png","path":null,"size":677.87,"width":750,"height":569,"sizeInBytes":677867},"thumbnail":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/thumbnail_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea.png","hash":"thumbnail_cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea","mime":"image/png","name":"thumbnail_cb2026-demo-trial-2026-03-02.png","path":null,"size":65.61,"width":206,"height":156,"sizeInBytes":65608}},"hash":"cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea","ext":".png","mime":"image/png","size":575.32,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/cb2026_demo_trial_2026_03_02_a4d69b91ea.png","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-03T04:48:18.465Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T04:48:18.465Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T04:48:18.470Z","focalPoint":null},"smallscreen":{"id":271,"documentId":"z6h6g03gcrmr538auc0nn5yz","name":"demo-trial-mobile-bg-2026-03-04.png","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":680,"height":768,"formats":{"small":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/small_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7.png","hash":"small_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7","mime":"image/png","name":"small_demo-trial-mobile-bg-2026-03-04.png","path":null,"size":352.48,"width":443,"height":500,"sizeInBytes":352481},"medium":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/medium_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7.png","hash":"medium_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7","mime":"image/png","name":"medium_demo-trial-mobile-bg-2026-03-04.png","path":null,"size":739.09,"width":664,"height":750,"sizeInBytes":739092},"thumbnail":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/thumbnail_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7.png","hash":"thumbnail_demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7","mime":"image/png","name":"thumbnail_demo-trial-mobile-bg-2026-03-04.png","path":null,"size":44.21,"width":138,"height":156,"sizeInBytes":44212}},"hash":"demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7","ext":".png","mime":"image/png","size":546.2,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/demo_trial_mobile_bg_2026_03_04_7fde4022f7.png","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:21.528Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:21.528Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-04T18:16:21.528Z","focalPoint":null}},"__component":"shared.demo-trial"},{"id":4023,"body":" Part 2: The Anatomy of Winning Ads
","class":"part-2-what-types-of-ads","name":"Part 2: The Anatomy of Winning Ads","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":171,"type":"youtube","external_video_id":"0QE6OifIlIM","title":null,"padding_top":null,"must_be_unlocked_to_render":false,"muted":false,"class":null,"playback_speed":"x1.00","button_preamble":null,"poster_label":null,"name":null,"body":null,"hide_controls":null,"autoplay":null,"loop":null,"identity":null,"__component":"shared.video"},{"id":4024,"body":"# What types of ads should you be testing?\n\nIf ad performance works like probability, then not all ads have the same odds of success. Some formats, hooks, and types of assets surface winners more often than others. \n\n**This is where an opportunity exists for creative strategists. There is no perfect formula for understanding what will get spend. The strength of a creative strategist is in understanding and interpreting the patterns behind what does.**\n\nThese patterns are what some might call “trending hooks” or “trending formats” or just “trends.” Instead of making recommendations based on a limited set of accounts, we’re able to look at how these formats are truly trending in aggregate. \n\nTwo simple measures — when considered together — help describe these patterns: hit rate and spend use ratio .","class":"no-padding-top","name":"What types of ads should you be testing?","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":4025,"body":"**Hit rate** looks at how often ads become winners. \nIt answers: _How frequently did this format become a winner?_\n\n**Spend use ratio** looks at where spend was concentrated. \nIt answers: _When we use this format, how likely is it to get spend?_\n\n How to read it:
\n\n- \\>1.0 → Format punches above its weight\n- ≈1.0 → Performs as expected\n- Why top visual styles differ by vertical
\n\nIt’s tempting to look at lists of “top-performing” or “trending” visual styles and treat them as universal advice. But advertising rarely behaves that neatly.\nWhen hit rates and spend use are broken down by vertical, patterns shift. A visual style that looks strong overall may perform well in one category and barely appear in others.","class":"bump-top","name":"Why top visual styles differ by vertical","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":231,"name":"chart-10","class":null,"chart":{"id":20,"documentId":"rvli3k4hk6hxnko5dq87vcky","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-chart-10","createdAt":"2026-03-03T06:00:20.462Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T06:00:20.462Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T06:00:21.089Z","title":"Chart 10","subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4030,"body":"In fashion, culturally fluent and playful visuals produce the most winners. In finance and professional services, credibility-forward formats and explanatory visuals dominate. And in home and lifestyle, demonstration and process matter more than anything else.\n\nFor creative strategists, this changes how benchmarks should be used. Cross-industry rankings are descriptive, but competitive context is better. Visual styles that surface winners or get spend in your specific vertical are often more meaningful than platform-wide recommendations.","class":"in-fashion","name":"In fashion, culturally fluent and playful visuals produce the most winners","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":8,"name":"Top hooks & headlines ","title":"Top hooks & headlines ","subtitle":"Like with visuals, it’s tempting to look for a list of “winning hooks.” But hook performance also depends on context.","body":null,"class":"top-hooks","mode":"slider-infinite","image_aspect_ratio":null,"autoscroll":true,"scroll_speed":null,"layout":"default","data":{"pill":{"label":"Hit Rate","value":"---","valuePostfix":"%"}},"hidden":null,"media":[{"i