":"Bold claim","anchor_href":null,"anchor_target":"_self","data":{"pill":{"value":"7.19"}},"body":null,"hide":null,"file":{"id":304,"documentId":"qekvz7mdraw066i1pg115ciq","name":"thh-010-bold-claim.png","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":314,"height":560,"formats":{"small":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/small_thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4.png","hash":"small_thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4","mime":"image/png","name":"small_thh-010-bold-claim.png","path":null,"size":254.17,"width":280,"height":500,"sizeInBytes":254167},"thumbnail":{"ext":".png","url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/thumbnail_thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4.png","hash":"thumbnail_thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4","mime":"image/png","name":"thumbnail_thh-010-bold-claim.png","path":null,"size":30.19,"width":87,"height":156,"sizeInBytes":30188}},"hash":"thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4","ext":".png","mime":"image/png","size":220.31,"url":"https://runt-media.motionapp.com/strapi/thh_010_bold_claim_9f81b833f4.png","previewUrl":null,"provider":"strapi-provider-cloudflare-r2","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-27T20:06:35.878Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-27T20:06:35.878Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-27T20:06:35.878Z","focalPoint":null}}],"__component":"shared.media-gallery"},{"id":232,"name":"Hook Headline Tactics","class":null,"chart":{"id":22,"documentId":"zpbxtj0kzql5lgb5a5972pq5","name":"creative-benchmarks-2026-hook-headline-tactics","createdAt":"2026-03-03T06:16:18.109Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-03T06:16:18.109Z","publishedAt":"2026-03-03T06:16:18.452Z","title":"Creative Benchmarks 2026 Hook Headline Tactics","subtitle":null},"__component":"shared.chart"},{"id":4031,"body":"Looking across both hit rate and spend use, certain themes appear repeatedly.\n\nHooks that signal immediacy, clarity, or a concrete reason to act tend to surface often. Language tied to price framing, offers, urgency, and product newness reduces the effort required to understand the value of the ad. \n\nOther hooks rely less on direct offers and more on attention. Curiosity, confessional framing, bold claims, or unexpected statements can interrupt scrolling and create tension or surprise. \n\nIt is also telling what appears less often near the top of these rankings. Broad lifestyle statements and vague benefit claims are common in advertising, but they surface less frequently among winners in this dataset. Messages that delay clarity or require more interpretation may struggle when attention is limited. \n\nKeep in mind that these patterns are time-bound. The dataset includes heavy promotional periods (BFCM & the holidays), when shoppers are primed for deals and product announcements. \n\nHooks and headlines that emphasize immediacy or value naturally align with what shoppers expect during this window. In a different season, it’s reasonable to expect that this looks very different — a point that warrants future analysis.","class":null,"name":"Looking across both hit rate and spend use, certain themes appear repeatedly.","title":null,"eyebrow":null,"layout":null,"__component":"shared.rich-text"},{"id":9,"name":"Top asset types","title":"Top asset types","subtitle":null,"body":"Asset choice is not only a creative decision. It is also an operational one. Some asset types are easier to adjust, remix, and relaunch. Others take more time and coordination to produce. That difference affects how quickly a team can test ideas and respond to performance signals.\n\nThe table below shows how different asset types appeared among winners and where spend concentrated.","class":"top-asset-types","mode":"slider-infinite","image_aspect_ratio":null,"autoscroll":true,"scroll_speed":null,"layout":"default","data":{"pill":{"label":"Hit Rate","value":"---","valuePostfix":"%"}},"hidden":null,"media":[{"id":87,"caption":null,"class":null,"title":"UGC","subtitle":null,"name":"UGC","anchor_href":"https://projects.motionapp.com/organization/69441477e6e360bb81e39da8/6944148b22af79295f